"Rakonczai J.","Global change and landscape change in Hungary",2007,"Geografia Fisica e Dinamica Quaternaria","30","2",,"229","232",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-55849108900&partnerID=40&md5=a357b4c7ffb65d861c4f7dc37fa80293","Department of Physical Geography and Geoinformatics, University of Szeged, Egyetem u. 2-6, H-6722 Szeged, Hungary","Rakonczai, J., Department of Physical Geography and Geoinformatics, University of Szeged, Egyetem u. 2-6, H-6722 Szeged, Hungary","Today, an increasing number of observations show that the effects of global climate change can be felt in Hungary. One important long term effect is the decrease of ground water. This paper uses test well data for a GIS model of ground water recession and the prediction of water deficits on the Danube-Tisza Interfluve in Hungary, where the detail of recession is closely related to topography. Consequent declines in biomass, examined using mutlispectral methods, after 25 % of this area. In the «Puszta» near Szabadkígyós a nature conservation area, within 25-years, unvegetated alkaline flats became covered by grass, former alkaline benches were totally eliminated by erosion, while grass and saline vegetation appeared.","Aridification; Biomass; Climate change; Danube-Tisza Interfiuve (Central Hungary); Groundwater change; Soil","aridification; biomass; climate change; GIS; global change; landscape; nature conservation; vegetation; Danube River; Eurasia; Europe; Tisza River",,,,,,"KOVÁCS, F., The investigation of regional variations in biomass production for the area of the Danube-Tisza interfluve using satellite image analysis (2005) Acta Geographica Szegediensis, 38, pp. 118-126; LÁNG, I., KISS, C.S., BAGI, A., (2006) A Nemzeti éghajlatváltozási stratégia koncepciójának alapjai (fundamentals of the concept of National Climate Change Strategy), , Budapest, 38 pp; RAKONCZAI, J., A Szabadkígyósi Tájvédelmi Könet talajviszonyai (Soils in the Szabadkígyós Protec ted Landscape) (1986) 